Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ColorSensor
    Class to hold all methods related to reading RGB color values from light sensor and determining the String representation of the color.
    LightLocalization
    Class which holds all the methods to perform light localization at a given location.
    Main
    The main driver class for the lab.
    Navigation
    Class to handle basic navigation methods and navigating between waypoints.
    Obstacle
    Class to hold all the methods required for identify an approaching obstacle, identify if that object is an actual obstacle, another EV3 robot, or the stranded vehicle.
    Odometer
    Class to handle the odometer methods.
    Reading
    Class to hold a basic value object coming from the US sensor.
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    StrandedVehicle
    Class to handle the methods responsible for picking up or hooking the stranded vehicle once it has been detected and identified.
    UltrasonicSensor
    Class to manage and record values of the ultrasonic sensor.
